    "locked": false,
    "title": "[mxfp4] Fix Hopper scale padding mask",
    "user": {
      "login": "hthu",
      "id": 2225756,
      "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjIyMjU3NTY=",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2225756?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/hthu",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/hthu",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hthu/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hthu/following{/other_user}",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hthu/gists{/gist_id}",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hthu/starred{/owner}{/repo}",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hthu/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hthu/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hthu/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hthu/events{/privacy}",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/hthu/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "user_view_type": "public",
      "site_admin": false
    },
    "body": "## Why\r\n\r\nHopper MXFP4 weight-scale swizzling can introduce padded scale bytes when the RHS K dimension does not fill the final scale tile.\r\n\r\nThe regular RHS value load already masks invalid K-tail values, but the Hopper scale path was loading and unswizzling the full scale tile without clearing invalid K-scale columns. If those padded scale bytes contain non-zero data, the matmul result can become sensitive to padding contents.\r\n\r\n## What is included\r\n\r\n* Masks invalid K-scale columns after `unswizzle_mxfp4_scale_hopper` in the regular matmul kernel.\r\n* Applies the same padding handling in the persistent/TMA matmul kernel.\r\n* Adds Hopper-only regression coverage for RHS MXFP4 scale padding:\r\n  * uses `k=1504`, which gives 47 MXFP scale columns and forces Hopper scale-layout K padding;\r\n  * uses `n=256`, one full Hopper N tile, to avoid testing unrelated N padding;\r\n  * dirties swizzled scale padding bytes with `0xFF`;\r\n  * verifies clean vs dirty scale-padding outputs are bit-exact;\r\n  * covers both regular and persistent/TMA opt-flag paths when applicable.\r\n\r\n## Test plan\r\n- Tested on my gpu setup with unit tests and real models on hopper devices\r\n",
